caption: Oh, what a wonderful place! The first thing you notice when you in there is that they are completely new. The waiter sits you at the table and brings tasty hot tea while you're browsing the menu. Everything on the menu is reasonably priced. I opted for some appetizers and an entree and was not disappointed. They were all delicious! Oh, the Thai BBQ ribs... The service was very humble, attentive and accommodating. I truly felt like I was being welcomed by the entire place. The manager (maybe owner) made his business to come over our table and ask if everything was to our satisfaction. And then they surprised me again. They offered a delicious ice cream dessert for free and my friend. I was told that I could have as much as I want. I asked for a second serving and was not turned down. The waiter was happy to bring me one! We left with an atmosphere, and joy. We were happy to leave 20% tip. On my way out I mentioned that they will get an unbiased review on Google and that's exactly what I'm doing right now. Visit this place and you will not be disappointed!
Great food, fast service a d great price..

I have been ordering at least two to three times in week since 2 months ago. And each time, I'll order at least 2 meals to meet the delivery min of $15. But today, what surprise me was one of the dinner is undercooked "Ipoh sauteed rice cake cube" contact owner explained is not edible he goes, we are busy we can't make you a new order. But I'll flagged the kitchen chef to do better next time.. wth??? I'm having dinner so the other person don't have to eat? You know what, goodbye 👋. Your won't have my business anymore!!
Very tasty authentic Asian cuisine, that’s fresh and reasonably priced ! I will definitely be returning and recommending.

I gave this place a chance.  I really did.  The Roti Canai sauce had a thick layer of oil on top which had to be drained to get to the actual sauce.  The texture of the chicken in the sauce tasted like it was deep fried prior to being added instead of stewed which is the norm.  The chicken itself is questionable – hoping it’s not pork.  The roti isn’t the paper-thin crispy round 12-inch in diameter fresh roti you’d expect.  It was 5-inches in diameter and dripping with oil inside and out.  Perhaps it was frozen and then deep fried?  The coconut rice had a strange green hue.  Why? And it didn’t taste like coconut rice.  The Kang Kung Belachan tasted okay, until it didn’t.  It was gritty and sandy.  Were these greens cleaned thoroughly?  These dishes are Malaysian-style not Malaysian and would probably appeal to some people who enjoy super oily food.  The staff was nice and the delivery was prompt.  Perhaps this was just a one-time coincidence with my particular order.  Everything looked and tasted quite unappetizing.  Wasting food isn’t my thing but I had to chuck it after a few bites.  I gave this place a chance however, the food speaks for itself.

This Malaysia restaurant just open one month ago. The food is good and authentic. Chicken satay is very tender. Beef satay is also flavored. Nasi Lemah is decent. The owner is nice and friendly. Highly recommend!

I’ve been there twice and went back for their satay. I would say their satay is the best in NYC. It is not those dried and chewy plain children breast but juicy and tasty with very rich lemongrass flavor. I also had their curry noodle soups and Hainanese Chicken too. Their food are above standard for sure. It is outstanding food but the price is a lot cheaper than Nyonya. I am glad there is a great Malaysian restaurant in my area.

Chinese home cooking at its best, if you are tired of the generic and overpriced standard Chinese restaurant fares expected like the one across the street from Tasty Gardens, hop in to this mom and pop's store for that fiery taste. Do be aware because this is a smaller operation, not all dishes may be available and some calling ahead may be required.
